33:33.000 --> 34:02.000
In the case when the manager makes a justified decision in the condition of risk, it is very important for him to reduce the number of basic components that are involved in the decision.

34:03.000 --> 34:29.000
The number of components, the criteria that are involved in determining the outcome, that is, to simplify the situation. Then it will be easier to assess the degree of susceptibility to possible losses or to assess the possibility of obtaining certain benefits.

34:29.000 --> 34:42.000
We have already said the word alternative more than once, that is, an option of possible solutions.

34:59.000 --> 35:26.000
The least risky alternative is the one that is more confident in the judgments of the outcome, where it is possible to more accurately assess the degree of risk.

35:26.000 --> 35:53.000
The most acceptable or the least risky alternative is the one that gives the most benefit in the event of an offensive.

35:53.000 --> 36:06.000
Accordingly, the least losses and the least possibility of being subject to an adverse outcome.

36:23.000 --> 36:44.000
This is the goal of the decision-making theory.

36:45.000 --> 36:57.000
This is not an easy task. In fact, the formation of efficiency criteria is one of the most complex problems in the theory and practice of management.

36:57.000 --> 37:07.000
It is connected with the transformation of goals and the ideal vision of the person making the decision in measurable quantities.

37:07.000 --> 37:22.000
That is, we emphasize once again that the criteria are set by the person making the decision, based on their preferences.

37:22.000 --> 37:36.000
I highlight two areas of practical application of the criteria.

37:36.000 --> 37:52.000
In the first case, they are used to assess the actual events. And the second is used in the process of making decisions to assess future outcomes.

37:52.000 --> 38:09.000
In both cases, the essential characteristics remain the same. That is, the purpose of the efficiency criteria is to measure the properties and relations in the system.

38:09.000 --> 38:21.000
The second general point is the orientation to the final goal and task of the organization, including its mission.

38:21.000 --> 38:35.000
If we talk about the criteria for assessing the future, then here it is necessary to note two points.

38:35.000 --> 38:58.000
The first is that as we move into the future, the uncertainty of the situation increases and the information potential decreases.

38:58.000 --> 39:07.000
That is, we can only estimate the probability of the onset of one or another event.

39:07.000 --> 39:32.000
And the second point is that as the predicted period increases, that is, we predict for a year, two or twenty years, the number of various alternatives increases many times.

39:32.000 --> 39:47.000
This is objective. There is no point in fighting this, but you need to be ready for this and form the efficiency criteria accordingly.

39:47.000 --> 40:00.000
There are four basic principles for forming the efficiency criteria.

40:00.000 --> 40:13.000
The first one says that in the conditions of a systemic crisis in the economy, the corresponding system of criteria and restrictions is required to solve the problems that have arisen.

40:13.000 --> 40:36.000
The second principle is that the formation of a system of criteria and restrictions must correspond to the principle of consistent reduction of uncertainty.

40:36.000 --> 41:03.000
The third principle says that the formation of efficiency criteria, as we have already said above, must be necessarily associated with and conditioned by the mission of the organization and its ultimate goals.

41:03.000 --> 41:25.000
And the last principle, the fourth principle, says that the system of efficiency criteria must be organically integrated into the human-machine system.

41:25.000 --> 41:52.000
Of course, the human component in these systems is decisive, but for complex, multi-plan solutions, oriented towards the long-term perspective, it is not possible to make a decision without taking part in the process.

41:55.000 --> 42:02.000
This is the main advantage of modern information technology.

42:02.000 --> 42:15.000
In addition to the principles, there are certain conditions for forming the efficiency criteria.

42:15.000 --> 42:32.000
