Such a graphical image of the solutions, states and consequences

01:12:21.000 --> 01:12:26.000
helps to make the right decision.

01:12:28.000 --> 01:12:35.000
To analyze the consequences, it is necessary to introduce something like a common denominator,

01:12:35.000 --> 01:12:38.000
namely, the criteria for assessment.

01:12:38.000 --> 01:12:43.000
These criteria can be both objective and subjective,

01:12:43.000 --> 01:12:51.000
that is, a certain kind of judgment and preference of the person making the decision.

01:12:52.000 --> 01:13:00.000
If, as we said, the goal of making the decision is not one,

01:13:00.000 --> 01:13:08.000
then in this case, the tree of solutions should be built on several models.

01:13:08.000 --> 01:13:20.000
We have received a number of alternatives for making decisions.

01:13:20.000 --> 01:13:30.000
It is advisable to build them in a certain hierarchical order, that is, according to priorities.

01:13:31.000 --> 01:13:39.000
Perhaps, they can be given a negative rating, starting from 0, which is extremely undesirable,

01:13:39.000 --> 01:13:45.000
to 10, which is considered excellent, absolutely acceptable.

01:13:45.000 --> 01:13:55.000
Thus, again, between a number of alternatives, you can choose the most favorable one.

01:13:55.000 --> 01:14:04.000
The construction of the tree of solutions is not as simple as it may seem at first glance.

01:14:04.000 --> 01:14:13.000
The fact is that, as you can see from the diagram,

01:14:13.000 --> 01:14:19.000
the probability of the onset of certain consequences is calculated.

01:14:19.000 --> 01:14:25.000
But as for determining the probability of the onset of these consequences,

01:14:25.000 --> 01:14:30.000
the task is not always easy, and sometimes it is impossible to fulfill.

01:14:30.000 --> 01:14:36.000
Therefore, in practice, when building a tree of solutions,

01:14:36.000 --> 01:14:41.000
two methods are used.

01:14:41.000 --> 01:14:51.000
If it is possible to obtain statistical data and calculate the probability of certain consequences,

01:14:51.000 --> 01:14:59.000
then the task is simplified and the solution is more reasonable.

01:14:59.000 --> 01:15:09.000
If this is not possible, then the probability values can be given in the assumed order,

01:15:09.000 --> 01:15:16.000
which, as you understand, significantly reduces the objectivity of the decision.

01:15:16.000 --> 01:15:24.000
What is the meaning and value of the tree of solutions?

01:15:24.000 --> 01:15:31.000
First of all, it is that the model clearly shows

01:15:31.000 --> 01:15:37.000
what consequences certain solutions may have,

01:15:37.000 --> 01:15:45.000
and certain events, and thus help the person making the decision

01:15:45.000 --> 01:15:54.000
to structure his thoughts, see the general picture of the development of the problem,

01:15:54.000 --> 01:15:59.000
and the consequences of making a decision.

01:15:59.000 --> 01:16:08.000
The next method is the cause-and-effect analysis.

01:16:08.000 --> 01:16:19.000
We talked a little about it when we were considering the course of the method of making management decisions.

01:16:19.000 --> 01:16:27.000
But then we were interested in how the method allows us to analyze

01:16:27.000 --> 01:16:36.000
the cause-and-effect connections between the data and the events during the study.

01:16:36.000 --> 01:16:41.000
When preparing a management decision,

01:16:41.000 --> 01:16:47.000
the cause-and-effect analysis plays an extremely important role and importance.

01:16:47.000 --> 01:16:59.000
Its main goal is to identify the cause-and-effect connections between the conditions and events,

01:16:59.000 --> 01:17:04.000
to see what is due to what,

01:17:04.000 --> 01:17:11.000
and, based on this analysis, to determine the dependence of some variables on others.

01:17:11.000 --> 01:17:23.000
Since there are no simple events in the world,

01:17:23.000 --> 01:17:27.000
let's say, two-level events,

01:17:27.000 --> 01:17:34.000
and, as a rule, this forms a whole chain of causes and effects,

01:17:34.000 --> 01:17:49.000
the cause-and-effect analysis aims to determine the hierarchy of these causes and effects,

01:17:49.000 --> 01:17:56.000
which starts from the point of the current state, the initial state,

01:17:56.000 --> 01:18:10.000
and leads back to the point where the problem needs to be diagnosed in order to be solved.

