Then, the problem of a snow coma actually arose,

01:19:06.000 --> 01:19:15.000
but the importance and value of such a scheme is to solve not only this minute problem,

01:19:15.000 --> 01:19:24.000
but also to determine the causes of this problem in order to correct the situation.

01:19:24.000 --> 01:19:33.000
When conducting an analysis, it is very important to follow a certain sequence.

01:19:33.000 --> 01:19:44.000
And as I have repeatedly said, repeating the theorists in the field of decision-making,

01:19:44.000 --> 01:19:50.000
the most important thing is a correctly, clearly formulated problem.

01:19:51.000 --> 01:19:59.000
Then, there is a mandatory identification of the cause or several causes of the problem,

01:19:59.000 --> 01:20:08.000
an explanation of the circumstances that caused the problem, and then a check of the significance,

01:20:08.000 --> 01:20:16.000
that is, whether the connection of two variables is statistically significant or not.

01:20:17.000 --> 01:20:28.000
When we talk about statistics, about the assessment of probability states,

01:20:28.000 --> 01:20:40.000
it is necessary to mention the so-called mistakes of the first and second order,

01:20:40.000 --> 01:20:48.000
which are important not only for the cause of the investigative analysis when solving problems,

01:20:48.000 --> 01:20:53.000
but also in a number of other life situations.

01:20:53.000 --> 01:21:04.000
The mistake of the first order is that the conclusion is made about the truth of some statement,

01:21:04.000 --> 01:21:11.000
when this statement is not true.

01:21:11.000 --> 01:21:15.000
For example, if we talk about the cause of the investigative analysis,

01:21:15.000 --> 01:21:20.000
then you can mistakenly conclude that two variables are connected to each other,

01:21:20.000 --> 01:21:25.000
while in fact there is no connection between them.

01:21:26.000 --> 01:21:34.000
The mistake of the second order is that you consider some statement to be untrue,

01:21:34.000 --> 01:21:38.000
while it is actually true.

01:21:38.000 --> 01:21:44.000
That is, if we talk about the cause of the investigative analysis,

01:21:44.000 --> 01:21:49.000
then we conclude in the case of the second order of the mistake

01:21:49.000 --> 01:21:57.000
that two variables are not connected, but they are actually connected to each other.

01:22:00.000 --> 01:22:06.000
Usually, the mistake of the first order is considered more serious,

01:22:06.000 --> 01:22:11.000
trying to reduce the probability of its conclusion.

01:22:12.000 --> 01:22:27.000
And minimizing the possibility of the occurrence of a mistake of the first order is much more important

01:22:27.000 --> 01:22:33.000
than reducing the probability of the second order.

01:22:33.000 --> 01:22:39.000
Maybe it doesn't look very clear. Let's try to illustrate this with examples.

01:22:42.000 --> 01:22:50.000
The division of error solutions into mistakes of the first and second order

01:22:50.000 --> 01:22:56.000
is also caused by the fact that the consequences of different types of error solutions

01:22:56.000 --> 01:23:03.000
are fundamentally different in that the lost win

01:23:04.000 --> 01:23:11.000
has less impact on the situation than the won win.

01:23:11.000 --> 01:23:18.000
For example, for a stockbroker, the consequences of not buying the stock

01:23:18.000 --> 01:23:25.000
